commentTextItems.html: <b> and that's the way to finish things!<b> McBrine drops a little short and its pulled to the mid-wicket boundary and Afghanistan win!

commentPostTextItems.html: Its only taken 23.5 overs for Afghanistan to knock off the 125 runs that they needed to win today.
Since they came back from Lunch, both Ihsanullah and Shahidi played beautifully to put together a 74 run partnership.
Ireland needed to attack in the field and so it meant that there was lots of gaps out there, they knew that Ireland's only chance of getting back into the game was taking wickets.
So by finding the gaps, with the odd boundary or two was always going to see them home.
Ireland used their most experienced bowlers, yet with the sun beating down they couldn't find the movement that the Afghan bowlers found early on in the day.
I'm sure that Ireland are regretting batting first now today, the life of a Captain eh?
Afghanistan go 2-1 up in the series and claim the series, after already winning the T20's last week its safe to say that its been a very prodictive trip to the Emerald Isle.
We are just waiting for the presentation to get ready, hopefully we will be able to find out who the player of the series is.
After taking 8 wickets in the series, Rashid Khan has been named player of the series.
Its quite fitting that the series finishes here on the last day of summer. The Irish International Home season is now over.
Although there are still a couple more games in the Ireland Domestic interpro series, so hopefully you will be able to join us then.
Its been a great series to cover and I hope that you have enjoyed our coverage of the games, its been a real pleasure to bring them too you.
Until next time this is Justin Smyth saying goodbye from Stormont.

gets forward, blocks the ball back down the pitch
whips through the shot and plays it back to the bowler

commentTextItems.html: punches the ball down the ground, its in front of mid-off and they run through for the single. 3 needed
goes round the wicket, its on the batters hip and he glances it down to long leg
Chase goes short, the bat is brought up and he helps the ball round to square leg
outside off-stump, shoulders arms and lets the ball go through to the keeper. Only one big hit away now
comes round the wicket and bowls it short, Shahidi isn't going to miss out on that and pulls it hard to cow corner
late cuts the ball down towards the third man boundary, target is down now to single figures

dismissalText.commentary: Tim Murtagh lbw b Rashid Khan 2 (13b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 15.38

dismissalComment.html: Murtagh plays back to the ball and it seems to keep a little low. The ball hits him on the pad and Nelson strikes. Ireland now 8 down.

dismissalText.long: c Aftab Alam b Mohammad Nabi
dismissalText.commentary: Andy McBrine c Aftab Alam b Mohammad Nabi 16 (50b 1x4 0x6 72m) SR: 32

dismissalComment.html: McBrine goes for the reverse sweep, he hits it well and doesn't get much power on the ball. Alam dives full length at short third man and takes a brilliant catch. Ireland are 9 down

milestones.description: This is the lowest match aggregate (251) involving teams Ireland & Afghanistan in ODIs
Paul Stirling has broken the record for most ducks (9) in ODIs for IRE, going past Porterfield's 9
Gulbadin Naib has broken the record for most ducks (5) in ODIs for AFG, going past Dawlat Zadran's 5
